es to ignore, their \"minimum\"/\"maximum\", \"const\"/\"enum\")\n16:     - [victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2](jsonschema-module-swagger-2) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (2.x) `@Schema` annotations\n17: - the [victools/jsonschema-maven-plugin](jsonschema-maven-plugin) – allowing you to generate JSON Schemas as part of your Maven build\n18: \n19: Another example for such a module is:\n20: - [imIfOu/jsonschema-module-addon](https://github.com/imIfOu/jsonschema-module-addon) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from a custom annotation with various parameters, which is part of the module.\n21: \n22: ----\n---\n14:     - [victools/jsonschema-module-javax-validation](jsonschema-module-javax-validation) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `javax.validation` annotations (e.g. which properties are nullable or not, their \"minimum\"/\"maximum\", \"minItems\"/\"maxItems\", \"minLength\"/\"maxLength\")\n15:     - [victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-1.5](jsonschema-module-swagger-1.5) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (1.5.x) annotations (e.g. \"description\", property name overrides, what properties to ignore, their \"minimum\"/\"maximum\", \"const\"/\"enum\")\n16:     - [victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2](jsonschema-module-swagger-2) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (2.x) `@Schema` annotations\n17: - the [victools/jsonschema-maven-plugin](jsonschema-maven-plugin) – allowing you to generate JSON Schemas as part of your Maven build\n18: \n19: Another example for such a module is:\n20: - [imIfOu/jsonschema-module-addon](https://github.com/imIfOu/jsonschema-module-addon) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from a custom annotation with various parameters, which is part of the module.\n21: \n22: ----\n23: \n---\n29: ----\n30: \n31: ## Usage\n32: ### Dependency (Maven)\n33: \n34: ```xml\n35: <dependency>\n36:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n37:     <artifactId>jsonschema-generator</artifactId>\n38:     <version>5.0.0</version>\n---\n32: ### Dependency (Maven)\n33: \n34: ```xml\n35: <dependency>\n36:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n37:     <artifactId>jsonschema-generator</artifactId>\n38:     <version>5.0.0</version>\n39: </dependency>\n40: ```\n41: \n---\n36:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n37:     <artifactId>jsonschema-generator</artifactId>\n38:     <version>5.0.0</version>\n39: </dependency>\n40: ```\n41: \n42: Since version `4.7`, the release versions of the main generator library and the (standard) `victools` modules listed above are aligned.\n43: It is recommended to use identical versions for all of them to ensure compatibility.\n44: \n45: It is discouraged to use an older/lower `jsonschema-generator` version than any of your `jsonschema-module-*` dependencies. If the module uses any feature only added to the `jsonschema-generator` in the newer version, runtime errors are to be expected.\n---\n48: #### Complete/Minimal Example\n49: ```java\n50: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.OptionPreset;\n51: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGenerator;\n52: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfig;\n53: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n54: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n55: import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n---\n49: ```java\n50: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.OptionPreset;\n51: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGenerator;\n52: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfig;\n53: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n54: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n55: import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n---\n50: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.OptionPreset;\n51: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGenerator;\n52: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfig;\n53: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n54: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n55: import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n59: SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n---\n52: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfig;\n53: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n54: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n55: import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n59: SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n60: SchemaGenerator generator = new SchemaGenerator(config);\n61: JsonNode jsonSchema = generator.generateSchema(YourClass.class);\n---\n55: import tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n59: SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n60: SchemaGenerator generator = new SchemaGenerator(config);\n61: JsonNode jsonSchema = generator.generateSchema(YourClass.class);\n62: \n63: System.out.println(jsonSchema.toPrettyString());\n64: ```\n---\n56: ```\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n59: SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n60: SchemaGenerator generator = new SchemaGenerator(config);\n61: JsonNode jsonSchema = generator.generateSchema(YourClass.class);\n62: \n63: System.out.println(jsonSchema.toPrettyString());\n64: ```\n65: \n---\n57: ```java\n58: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2020_12, OptionPreset.PLAIN_JSON);\n59: SchemaGeneratorConfig config = configBuilder.build();\n60: SchemaGenerator generator = new SchemaGenerator(config);\n61: JsonNode jsonSchema = generator.generateSchema(YourClass.class);\n62: \n63: System.out.println(jsonSchema.toPrettyString());\n64: ```\n65: \n66: Additional examples can be found in the [jsonschema-examples](jsonschema-examples) folder or throughout the various tests classes.\n---\n\n--- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/v5.0.0/jsonschema-module-swagger-2/README.md\n1: # Java JSON Schema Generator – Module Swagger (2.x)\n2: [![Maven Central](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2/badge.svg)](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2)\n3: \n4: Module for the [jsonschema-generator](../jsonschema-generator) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (2.x) annotations\n5: \n6: ## Features\n7:  1. From `@Schema(description = …)` on types in general, derive `\"description\"`.\n---\n1: # Java JSON Schema Generator – Module Swagger (2.x)\n2: [![Maven Central](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2/badge.svg)](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2)\n3: \n4: Module for the [jsonschema-generator](../jsonschema-generator) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (2.x) annotations\n5: \n6: ## Features\n7:  1. From `@Schema(description = …)` on types in general, derive `\"description\"`.\n8:  2. From `@Schema(title = …)` on types in general, derive `\"title\"`.\n---\n1: # Java JSON Schema Generator – Module Swagger (2.x)\n2: [![Maven Central](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2/badge.svg)](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2)\n3: \n4: Module for the [jsonschema-generator](../jsonschema-generator) – deriving JSON Schema attributes from `swagger` (2.x) annotations\n5: \n6: ## Features\n7:  1. From `@Schema(description = …)` on types in general, derive `\"description\"`.\n8:  2. From `@Schema(title = …)` on types in general, derive `\"title\"`.\n9:  3. From `@Schema(ref = …)` on types in general, replace subschema with `\"$ref\"` to external/separate schema (except for the main type being targeted).\n10:  4. From `@Schema(subTypes = …)` on types in general, derive `\"anyOf\"` alternatives.\n---\n46: ----\n47: \n48: ## Documentation\n49: JavaDoc is being used throughout the codebase, offering contextual information in your respective IDE or being available online through services like [javadoc.io](https://www.javadoc.io/doc/com.github.victools/jsonschema-module-swagger-2).\n50: \n51: Additional documentation can be found in the [Project Wiki](https://github.com/victools/jsonschema-generator/wiki).\n52: \n53: ----\n54: \n55: ## Usage\n---\n53: ----\n54: \n55: ## Usage\n56: ### Dependency (Maven)\n57: ```xml\n58: <dependency>\n59:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n60:     <artifactId>jsonschema-module-swagger-2</artifactId>\n61:     <version>[5.0.0,6.0.0)</version>\n62: </dependency>\n---\n55: ## Usage\n56: ### Dependency (Maven)\n57: ```xml\n58: <dependency>\n59:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n60:     <artifactId>jsonschema-module-swagger-2</artifactId>\n61:     <version>[5.0.0,6.0.0)</version>\n62: </dependency>\n63: ```\n64: \n---\n57: ```xml\n58: <dependency>\n59:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n60:     <artifactId>jsonschema-module-swagger-2</artifactId>\n61:     <version>[5.0.0,6.0.0)</version>\n62: </dependency>\n63: ```\n64: \n65: The release versions of the main generator library and this module are aligned.\n66: It is recommended to use identical versions for both dependencies to ensure compatibility.\n---\n59:     <groupId>com.github.victools</groupId>\n60:     <artifactId>jsonschema-module-swagger-2</artifactId>\n61:     <version>[5.0.0,6.0.0)</version>\n62: </dependency>\n63: ```\n64: \n65: The release versions of the main generator library and this module are aligned.\n66: It is recommended to use identical versions for both dependencies to ensure compatibility.\n67: \n68: ### Code\n---\n66: It is recommended to use identical versions for both dependencies to ensure compatibility.\n67: \n68: ### Code\n69: #### Passing into SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder.with(Module)\n70: ```java\n71: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n72: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n73: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.module.swagger2.Swagger2Module;\n74: ```\n75: ```java\n---\n68: ### Code\n69: #### Passing into SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder.with(Module)\n70: ```java\n71: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n72: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n73: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.module.swagger2.Swagger2Module;\n74: ```\n75: ```java\n76: Swagger2Module module = new Swagger2Module();\n77: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2019_09)\n---\n70: ```java\n71: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder;\n72: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.generator.SchemaVersion;\n73: import com.github.victools.jsonschema.module.swagger2.Swagger2Module;\n74: ```\n75: ```java\n76: Swagger2Module module = new Swagger2Module();\n77: SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder configBuilder = new SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder(SchemaVersion.DRAFT_2019_09)\n78