uidance shouldn't be too detailed or appear like an implementation plan, but might mention how to use Swagger2Module clearly without redundancy.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating Jackson dependencies**\\n\\nFor version 5, I should use the Jackson 3 API imports (`tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode`) instead of the Jackson 2 imports (`com.fasterxml...`). I need to be cautious about the risks, especially since the existing tests might fail with the outdated Jackson 2 import. It’s essential to align dependency versions, like keeping `jsonschema-generator` and the module at 5.0.0, and ensuring that swagger annotations match the parent version. Importantly, the target module's POM must declare these as provided. I should also ensure that the output is a valid single JSON and avoid any markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful tests need the main victools generator and Swagger annotation API because jsonschema-module-swagger-2 declares both as provided; v5 also migrated schema nodes to Jackson 3 tools.jackson types.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:5.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jsonschema-module-swagger-2 is only a module for SchemaGenerator and declares jsonschema-generator as a provided dependency, so tests must add the aligned generator artifact explicitly.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"io.swagger.core.v3:swagger-annotations:2.2.41\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module derives schema attributes from Swagger 2.x annotations and declares swagger-annotations as provided; tests defining @Schema/@ArraySchema models need the annotation API on the test classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property is indicated. For version 5.0.0, test code should use Jackson 3 imports such as `tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode` rather than Jackson 2 `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode`.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Reusing the 4.38.0 test imports unchanged is likely to keep failing javac because victools 5.0.0 migrated from Jackson 2 to Jackson 3 packages.\",\n    \"Keep the generator version aligned with the module version; older generator versions are explicitly discouraged by the upstream docs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05a586a6bfc83c21016a40453af92881978620c6363946b99c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7391, "output": 1268, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39891, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782596909978, "responseId": "resp_05a586a6bfc83c21016a40452e8688819782bc9485f5bbd7d0"}, "toolResults": []}
